A policy should exist defining the need to create information that is interoperable. This policy is often linked to a regional, national or organizational strategy for sharing and exchanging geographic information (e.g. INSPIRE in the EU11http://inspire.​ec.​europa.​eu/
, and LINZ in New Zealand22http://www.​linz.​govt.​nz/​about-​linz/​our-​location-​strategy/​connecting-​and-​sharing-​geospatial-​data
). Annex F presents best practice guidelines for data policy.
